



Sir
Monticello Sep. 3. 1772.



Inclosed is a copy of Dickies bill against you. You will be pleased to send me a state of the case as it is to be set forth in your answer. In this you should take care to answer every allegation and interrogatory. As soon as I recieve this I shall put it into the form of an answer and return it to you to be sworn to. I am Sir Your humble sert.,

Th: Jefferson

